# Commit messages

When generating a Git commit message (Cursor AI Commit / Source Control sparkle / agent commit), **output only** a Commitlint-valid [Conventional Commit](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/).

Enforced by `commitlint.config.js` on the Husky `commit-msg` hook.

## Format

```
<type>(optional-scope): <lowercase imperative subject>

- Bullet 1
- Bullet 2
```

No explanations, markdown fences, or “This commit…” prose.

## Types

`feat` | `fix` | `chore` | `docs` | `refactor` | `perf` | `test` | `build` | `ci` | `style` | `revert`

## Subject

- Lowercase; imperative (“add”, “fix”, “introduce”)
- No trailing period; prefer ≤72 chars; max **100**
- Never a bare title (`Update README`, `Fix bug`) — type prefix is required
- Type carries the verb class: `feat(…): add …` not `Add …` alone

## Scope (optional)

kebab-case only: `app`, `events`, `core`, `ai`, `tooling`, `brand`, `extension-sdk`, `backlog`

## Body

- One blank line after the subject
- `- ` bullets; every line ≤ **100** chars
- Why / notable deltas; calm JobJitsu voice

## Good

```
feat(events): add in-memory event bus

- Implement createInMemoryEventBus with ordered delivery
- Cover pub/sub and unsubscribe in unit tests
```

```
chore(tooling): configure commitlint husky and lint-staged
```

## Bad (never)

```
Add initial project structure and configuration files for JobJitsu
This commit establishes the foundational structure...
```

```
Update README with architecture details.
```

```
Implement ESLint and Prettier configurations, add commitlint for validation...
```
